Doctors Without Borders (MSF) nurse Bhelekazi Mdlalose prepares herself to perform a swab test for COVID-19 coronavirus on health workers at the Vlakfontein Clinic in Lenasia. JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has increased to 17,200. The death toll has jumped to 312 and total recoveries are at 7,960. READ: Schools to reopen on 1 June: Dept of Basic Education The Northern Cape has also recorded its first death. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize announced the new stats on Tuesday night.